# Teaching AI to Scaffold a .NET Clean Architecture Solution

Starting a new .NET project often feels like repeating the same steps over and over again:

- Create a solution  
- Add multiple projects  
- Configure references  
- Install NuGet packages  
- Enforce architectural guidelines  

Even if you're experienced, this process typically takes **10‚Äì15 minutes** every time.  

But what if you could automate all of it?  

Recently, I decided to experiment with **Agent Skills**‚Äîa way to teach AI coding agents how to perform specific development workflows. Instead of manually setting up the project structure, I created an Agent Skill that automates the entire scaffolding process for a **Clean Architecture-based .NET solution**.

