## What Are Agent Skills?

Agent Skills are **reusable workflows that extend AI coding agents with specialized capabilities**. Think of them as "playbooks" for AI‚Äîinstead of repeatedly explaining the same task to the assistant, you define a repeatable procedure that the agent can execute whenever needed.

A typical Agent Skill includes:

- Step-by-step instructions  
- Optional scripts or templates  
- Any resources required for the task  

When the AI detects a relevant task, it loads the skill and **executes the workflow automatically**. This concept is gaining traction in tools like **Visual Studio Code** through AI assistants like **GitHub Copilot**.  

For more details, check out [Command Code's documentation on Agent Skills](https://commandcode.ai/docs/skills/what-are-skills?utm_source=chatgpt.com).

